About Me

Hello, I am Mitch Hoesing

If interested, here is a short life summary thus far...



I'll start from my graduation of high school in 2009. Like most I was unsure of exactly what I wanted to do so I enrolled into community college and started studying Computer Science as it was a safe bet that I would end up in this field. I completed the two years and took a break to consider if I wanted to finish school or start a career in another field.

At some point during my break I came across a Twitch stream of the Magic: the Gathering (MTG) World Championship grand finals between Reid Duke and Shahar Shenhar. I had no idea what was going on in the game but I was intrigued and decided to visit my local MTG shop Top Deck Hobbies. Suprisingly, I learned that a guy I went to high school with owned the place. After some time frequenting the shop I was asked to help with some work and was eventually offered a job. Soon after it was expressed to me that the owner wanted to move the shop to Corvallis, Oregon right off of Oregon State University campus. I concurred that this was a smart business move and decided that I could finish my Computer Science degree at OSU at the same time. I managed this store for a couple years before deciding to leave to focus completely on school and finish my degree as the shop took a bit of my time.

I still had a year in my degree to finish and still needed to support myself financially so I decided to look for work on campus in a student job as they were flexible. Eventually I came across a position as an Assistant to the Industry Liaison for the School of Civil and Construction Engineering. The position required some Salesforce management work as well as industry event management and as I enjoyed management with Top Deck Hobbies I decided to apply. I got called for an interview and ended up getting the job. This position required me to work with many industry affiliates, professors, the school head and other various people in positions that required me to be professional in our interactions. I learned much about communication in this role and enjoyed my time here but after I graduated I could no longer hold a student position, so I searched for a job in my field of study.

Working at Ascentec Still unsure what I want to do but I love esports.
